Note 11: Income Taxes
The Company accounts for income taxes using the asset and liability approach as prescribed by SFAS No. 109, ("SFAS No. 109"). This approach requires the recognition of deferred tax assets and liabilities for the expected future tax consequences of events that have been included in the financial statements or tax returns. Using the enacted tax rates in effect for the year in which the differences are expected to reverse, deferred tax liabilities and assets are determined based on the differences between the financial reporting and the tax basis of an asset or liability.
